Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Make Best Flaky Pastry. Gather pastry into a ball. Shape into flattened round on lightly floured surface. Roll pastry, using floured rolling pin, into circle 2 inches larger than upside-down pie plate, 9x1 1/4 inches. Fold pastry into fourths; place in pie plate. Unfold and ease into plate, pressing firmly against bottom and side. Trim overhanging edge of pastry 1 inch from rim of pie plate. Fold and roll pastry under, even with plate; flute as desired. Beat sugar, margarine, corn syrup, salt, egg and egg whites in medium bowl with wire whisk or hand beater until well blended. Stir in oats and pecans. Pour into pastry-lined pie plate. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set; cool. Best Flaky Pastry: Mix flour and salt in medium bowl. Cut in shortening, using pastry blender or crisscrossing 2 knives, until particles are size of small peas. Sprinkle with cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost leaves side of bowl (1 to 2 teaspoons more water can be added if necessary).